One person and fifteen others were abducted when terrorists invaded Batagari village in Rafi local government area of Niger State. The attack took place in the early hours of Monday. The Nation learnt that the terrorists entered the town on motorcycles, shooting into the air.   EFCC re-arraigns Fani-Kayode on amended 17-count charge     We won’t pay ransom to free abducted commissioner –…     AFCON 2021: Okoye, Iwobi get death threats over Super Eagles…   The residents, who were getting ready for the day, ran into the bush but most of the women, who could not escape, were taken away by the terrorists. - Advertisement - A resident in the village told The Nation the bandits moved from one house to the other, taking away money and other valuables. Several family members said they were yet to get any information on the whereabouts of the abductees or any demand for ransom.